{
  "texts": [
    "This concatenated representation combines the information from all three levels of the hierarchy and is used as input to the scoring model.",
    "This two-stage neural network model showed prompt-independent AES model by reducing the impact of contents from the semantic embedding.",
    "POS embedding and non prompt-specific features for generalization: Ridley et al. (2020) proposed a neural network method that employs POS embedding to capture syntactic information from the essays and non prompt-specific features, such as length based, readability, sentiment, text complexity, and text variation.",
    "As it is shown in Fig. 16, essay inputs are first converted into part-of-speech (POS) embedding.",
    "Subsequently, convolutional recurrent neural networks and pooling methods are employed to extract syntactic features."
  ]
}